<introduction>
  <p>
    Use the Pythagorean identify (<m>\sin^2\theta+\cos^2\theta=1</m>) and the result from <xref ref="x3_3-ex1">Exercise</xref> to prove
          <me>
            \cos2\theta=2\cos^2\theta-1
          </me>
  </p>
</introduction>
Use the Pythagorean identify (<m>\sin^2\theta+\cos^2\theta=1</m>) and the result from <xref ref="x3_3-ex1">Exercise</xref> to prove
          <me>
            \cos2\theta=2\cos^2\theta-1
